SIMPLE: misgive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misgive
<hw>Mis*give"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Misgave</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Misgiven</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Misgiving</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To give or grant amiss.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Laud.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically: To give doubt and apprehension to,
instead of confidence and courage; to impart fear to; to make
irresolute; -- usually said of the mind or heart, and followed by the
objective personal pronoun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So doth my heart <qex>misgive</qex> me in these conflicts⟦br⟧
What may befall him, to his harm and ours.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such whose consciences <qex>misgave</qex> them, how ill they had
deserved.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To suspect; to dread.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misgive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misgive
<hw>Mis*give"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give out doubt and
apprehension; to be fearful or irresolute.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My mind
<xex>misgives</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>misgiving</ent>⟦br⟧
